title: Nobody knows who will win this election – and that is terrible news for Jeremy Corbyn
text:
This time will be different. Oh, in various respects the 2019 general election will hold to sacred and immortal traditions. The ceremonial prorogation of parliament will be immediately followed, for example, by someone dressed as a chicken chasing one or other of the party leaders around the country. There will then be the ritual launch of Labour’s leaflet claiming that a re-elected Conservative government will privatise the NHS.

But in other, more important, ways, this election campaign will not follow the pattern established by its predecessors, particularly the last contest from two and a half years ago. The 2017 general election was characterised by an assumption – widely held at the time,...
